    <string name="nfc_debug_developer_instructions">To enable advanced NFC debugging:\n\n1. Enable Developer Options\n   Settings > About Phone > tap \"Build Number\" 7 times\n\n2. Enable NFC\n   Settings > Connected Devices > Connection Preferences > NFC\n\n3. Enable NFC Debug Logging (Developer Options)\n   Settings > Developer Options > enable \"Enable verbose vendor logging\"\n   This captures low-level NFC controller logs in logcat.\n\n4. View NFC Logs via ADB\n   adb logcat -s NfcService NfcAdaptation NxpNci NxpHal\n\n5. In-App Debug\n   Use the \"Start NFC Test\" button above to capture tag details\n   and APDU responses directly in this screen.\n\nNote: Some NFC debug options may vary by device manufacturer and Android version.</string>
